==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Selion
<hw>Sel"ion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>seillon</ets> a measure of land, F. <ets>sillon</ets> a ridge,
furrow, LL. <ets>selio</ets> a measure of land.]</ety> <def>A short
piece of land in arable ridges and furrows, of uncertain quantity; also,
a ridge of land lying between two furrows.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seljukian</ent>⟦br⟧
